Legal Calculus 4.5 — Enhanced Modules — Module 24
📘 Legal Calculus — Module 24

Subpoenas — Rule 45 Basics & Objections

⚖️ Core Message

Subpoenas summon evidence from non‑parties; precision prevents quash.
📖 Lesson Content

1. Describe categories narrowly: timeframe, custodians, and terms.
2. Serve with witness fees when required; calendar compliance date.
3. Provide notice to all parties; address burden promptly if raised.
4. If objected, confer and adjust scope; then move to enforce with proof.
📝 Assignment

Draft a 1‑page subpoena schedule with three categories, date, place, and custodian list; add a short notice to parties.
✅ Model Response

SUBPOENA SCHEDULE (excerpt)

1. Emails (May–Aug 2025) of Custodians X/Y containing 'docket'/'timely'.

2. Call logs (July 20–Aug 5, 2025) for Clerk’s main line.

3. Policy manual excerpt on emergency filings.

Notice: Served on parties by email same day.

 

💡 Reflection Summary

Precision gets compliance; vagueness gets quash.
🎨 Visual Concept

A focused beam highlighting a narrow document slice.
